Continue increase in state investment in Higher Ed, increase state grants to make college more affordable for 100,000 students
.@UMNMedSchool included in our budget proposal & @SenateDFL budget.  Will fight for it in final bill.

MN ranks 2nd nationally for people 24-64 with associate degree or more. More education=lower unemployment.
77% of MN High School Grads go to college.  Good, but we need to do better.  Affordability will help.
Statewide, 87% of fulltime 1st year students receive some financial aid.  Affordability matters to students and families.
.@PrezKaler is right.  Governor Dayton and I reversed decade of cuts, investing $250M last session.  Higher Ed is our economy's engine.
